      "term": "Tabula Rasa",
      "type": "concept",
      "definition": "The mind is a blank slate at birth, shaped entirely by experience. There are no innate ideas or principles.",
      "source_id": "WD:Q1151067",
      "reference_urls": ["https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tabula_rasa"],
      "examples": ["Infants have no preconceived notions", "Knowledge is acquired, not given"],
